               <floruit notBefore="1400" notAfter="1499">He was  a monk of the 15th century who had  a connection to the royal family. 
                  He lived during the reigns of  
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>, 
                 
                  <persName ref="PRS2334BaedaM"> <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>  
                     Baʾǝda Māryām I</persName>,  
                  <persName ref="PRS3874eskender"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                     ʾƎskǝndǝr</persName> and 
                  <persName ref="PRS7481NaodA"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>  Nāʿod (ʾAnbasā Baḍar)
                </persName>. 
                He is said to have clashed with the <persName ref="PRS11211Stephanites">Stephanites</persName> clergy and to have been persecuted by their supporters.</floruit>
           
